UPDATE spells SET summary = 'Divine light radiates 30 feet around you. Creatures you choose shed dim light and have advantage on saves. Others have disadvantage on attacks against them. When a fiend or undead hits an affected creature with a melee attack, the attacker must succeed on a Constitution saving throw or be {@condition blinded} until the spell ends.' WHERE slug = 'holy-aura';
UPDATE spells SET summary = 'Create a Huge shadowy dragon. Enemies seeing it must succeed on a Wisdom save or become {@condition frightened} for 1 minute. As a bonus action, move it up to 60 feet and exhale {@damage 7d6} damage in a 60-foot cone (acid, cold, fire, lightning, necrotic, or poison). Creatures must make an Intelligence save, taking damage on a failed save or half on a success.' WHERE slug = 'illusory-dragon';
UPDATE spells SET summary = 'A swirling cloud of smoke and embers fills a 20-foot-radius sphere. Creatures in it must make a Dexterity save, taking {@damage 10d8} fire damage on a failed save or half on a success. A creature must also save when it enters the area for the first time on a turn or ends its turn there. Cloud moves 10 feet away from you at the start of each of your turns.' WHERE slug = 'incendiary-cloud';
UPDATE spells SET summary = 'Magical darkness spreads to fill a 60-foot-radius sphere. Darkvision doesn''t work in it, and nonmagical light and spells of 8th level or lower can''t illuminate the area. Shrieking and mad laughter fills the sphere. Whenever a creature starts its turn in the sphere, it must make a Wisdom save, taking {@damage 8d8} psychic damage on a failed save or half on a success.' WHERE slug = 'maddening-darkness';
UPDATE spells SET summary = 'Banish a creature you can see into a labyrinthine demiplane for the duration or until it escapes. The target can use its action to attempt to escape with a {@dc 20} Intelligence check. On success, it escapes. A minotaur or goristro automatically succeeds. When the spell ends, the target reappears in the space it left or the nearest unoccupied space.' WHERE slug = 'maze';
UPDATE spells SET summary = 'Stone fortress erupts from a square area 120 feet on each side. Four turrets (20 feet on a side, 30 feet tall) are connected by 80-foot stone walls with up to four doors. A 50-foot-square keep inside has three floors. Staff of 100 invisible servants obeys designated creatures. Each 10-foot-by-10-foot section of stone: AC 15, 30 hit points per inch of thickness, immune to poison and psychic damage.' WHERE slug = 'mighty-fortress';
UPDATE spells SET summary = 'Brilliant sunlight flashes in a 60-foot radius. Creatures must make a Constitution save. On a failed save, they take {@damage 12d6} radiant damage and are {@condition blinded} for 1 minute. On a successful save, they take half damage and aren''t blinded. Undead and oozes have disadvantage. Blinded creatures can retry the save at the end of each turn.' WHERE slug = 'sunburst';
UPDATE spells SET summary = 'Create a telepathic link with one willing familiar creature on the same plane. Until the spell ends, you and the target can instantaneously share words, images, sounds, and sensory messages. The target recognizes you as the creature it communicates with. A creature with an Intelligence of at least 1 understands your words.' WHERE slug = 'telepathy';
UPDATE spells SET summary = 'A wall of water appears up to 300 feet long, 300 feet high, and 50 feet thick. Creatures within must make a Strength save, taking {@damage 6d10} bludgeoning damage or half on a success. At the start of each turn, the wall moves 50 feet away and creatures in its path must save or take {@damage 5d10} bludgeoning damage. Wall height reduces by 50 feet each turn.' WHERE slug = 'tsunami';
UPDATE spells SET summary = 'You and up to eight willing creatures project astral bodies to the Astral Plane. Your material body is unconscious and doesn''t age. Your astral form has a silvery cord tether. If the cord is cut, you die instantly. Your astral form can travel the Astral Plane and pass through portals. Damage to the astral form doesn''t affect your physical body.' WHERE slug = 'astral-projection';
UPDATE spells SET summary = 'Create a 3-foot planar rift. Make up to two melee spell attacks ({@damage 4d12} force damage each). Crits on 18+, dealing extra {@damage 8d12} force damage ({@damage 12d12} total). As a bonus action, move it up to 30 feet and make up to two more attacks. The blade can pass through any barrier.' WHERE slug = 'blade-of-disaster';
UPDATE spells SET summary = 'Conjure a portal linking an unoccupied space you see to another plane. Portal is 5 to 20 feet in diameter and lasts for the duration. Travel is one-way to the other plane, appearing in the nearest unoccupied space. Deities can prevent the portal. You can speak a creature''s name; if on another plane, the portal opens near it and draws it through to your side.' WHERE slug = 'gate';
UPDATE spells SET summary = 'Restrain a creature with a Wisdom save (immune if it succeeds). While affected, the creature doesn''t need to breathe, eat, drink, or age. Divination spells can''t locate it. Choose one: Burial (entombed in a force sphere), Chaining (heavy chains restrain), Hedged Prison (tiny demiplane), Minimus Containment (shrinks to 1 inch, trapped in gemstone), or Slumber (falls asleep, can''t awaken).' WHERE slug = 'imprisonment';
UPDATE spells SET summary = 'Transform up to ten creatures into beast forms. Unwilling creatures must make a Wisdom save. New form must have CR equal to or less than the target''s (or half target''s level). Game stats are replaced by the beast''s but retain hit points, alignment, and personality. Gain temporary hit points equal to the beast form''s HP. Can''t speak, cast spells, or benefit from equipment.' WHERE slug = 'mass-polymorph';
UPDATE spells SET summary = 'Four blazing orbs strike four points you see. Each creates a 40-foot-radius sphere. Creatures must make a Dexterity save, taking {@damage 20d6} fire and {@damage 20d6} bludgeoning damage on a failed save or half on a success. A creature affected by more than one burst is affected only once. The spell damages objects and ignites flammable ones.' WHERE slug = 'meteor-swarm';
UPDATE spells SET summary = 'A multicolored wall (up to 90 feet long, 30 feet high, 1 inch thick) or sphere (up to 30 feet diameter) blocks an area. You and designated creatures pass through safely. Others within 20 feet must make a Constitution save or be {@condition blinded} for 1 minute. The wall has seven layers (red, orange, yellow, green, blue, indigo, violet), each with damage type and destruction method.' WHERE slug = 'prismatic-wall';
UPDATE spells SET summary = 'Up to ten creatures you see must make an Intelligence save. Creatures with Intelligence 2 or lower are unaffected. On a failed save, a target takes {@damage 14d6} psychic damage and is {@condition stunned}. On a successful save, half damage and not stunned. Killed targets'' heads explode. Stunned creatures can retry the save at the end of each turn.' WHERE slug = 'psychic-scream';
UPDATE spells SET summary = 'Assume form of a different creature with CR equal to your level or lower (not constructs or undead). You must have seen the creature type before. Game stats are replaced except you retain alignment and Intelligence, Wisdom, Charisma, skill proficiencies, and saving throw proficiencies. Use creature''s higher proficiency bonuses.' WHERE slug = 'shapechange';
UPDATE spells SET summary = 'Storm forms 360 feet wide. Creatures under it must make Constitution save, taking {@damage 2d6} thunder damage and becoming {@condition deafened} for 5 minutes.
Round 2: Acid rain ({@damage 1d6}). Round 3: Six lightning bolts ({@damage 10d6}). Round 4: Hail ({@damage 2d6}). Rounds 5-10: Freezing rain creates difficult terrain.' WHERE slug = 'storm-of-vengeance';
UPDATE spells SET summary = 'You briefly stop time for everyone except yourself. You take {@dice 1d4 + 1} turns in a row. The spell ends if your actions affect any creature other than yourself or worn/carried items, or if you move more than 1,000 feet from the casting location.' WHERE slug = 'time-stop';
UPDATE spells SET summary = 'Transform a creature or nonmagical object into another creature, a nonmagical object, or vice versa. An unwilling creature can make a Wisdom save to resist. The transformation lasts for the duration or until the target reaches 0 HP. If you concentrate for the full duration, it becomes permanent. Object into Creature: The creature''s size can''t exceed the object''s size.' WHERE slug = 'true-polymorph';
UPDATE spells SET summary = 'Touch a creature dead no longer than 200 years (not from old age). If its soul is free and willing, it''s restored with all hit points. The spell closes wounds, neutralizes poison, cures disease, and lifts curses. Missing organs and limbs are provided. If the original body is gone, speak the creature''s name and it appears nearby.' WHERE slug = 'true-resurrection';
UPDATE spells SET summary = 'Creatures in a 30-foot-radius sphere must make a Wisdom save. On a failed save, they become {@condition frightened} for the duration. The illusion manifests their worst nightmares. At the end of each frightened creature''s turn, it must succeed on a Wisdom save or take {@damage 4d10} psychic damage.' WHERE slug = 'weird';
UPDATE spells SET summary = 'The mightiest spell. Alter reality in accord with your desires by speaking aloud. Duplicate any spell of 8th level or lower without meeting requirements. Or create one effect: Create an object (up to 25,000 gp value, max 300 feet dimension); restore health to twenty creatures; grant damage resistance to ten creatures; grant spell/magic immunity to ten creatures for 8 hours; undo a recent event.' WHERE slug = 'wish';